What feels like a chain of unlikely “miracles” is usually what happens when three things stack:
	1.	Huge search space (tons of possible thoughts, connections, inputs)
	2.	Continuous filtering (you keep what “clicks”)
	3.	Retrospective framing (you only notice the hits, not the misses)

